label.value: epitope protection experiment based on survival

definition.value: An epitope protection experiment that determines the success of the epitope intervention based on increased survival of the host.

label.value: epitope treatment experiment

definition.value: An epitope intervention experiment that tests the ability of inducing an epitope immune response to treat an existing disease  in the host.

label.value: half maximal inhibitory concentration (IC50)

definition.value: Half maximal inhibitory concentration (IC50) is a scalar measurement datum that measures the effectiveness of a compound to competitively inhibit a given process, and corresponds to the concentration of the compound at which it reaches half of its maximum inhibitory effect.

label.value: epitope specific immune intervention

definition.value: An administration in vivo to either actively or passively immunize an organism in order to induce a response against a specific immune epitope

label.value: epitope specific cytokine production by T cells

definition.value: A process of cytokine production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: ELISPOT assay measuring epitope specific transforming growth factor-beta production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific transforming growth factor-beta production by T cells that uses an ELISPOT assay.

label.value: operator variation design

definition.value: A study design that assesses the operator performance and relation to data consistency and quality.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific IP-10 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific IP-10 production by T cells that uses a cytometric bead array assay.

label.value: comparative genome hybridization by array design

definition.value: A study design that detects genomic copy number variations using microarray technology.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-27 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-27 production by T cells.

label.value: in vivo design

definition.value: A study design that is conducted entirely in a living organism, e.g. a compound treatment in a mouse model.

label.value: genotyping by high throughput sequencing design

definition.value: A study design that classifies an individual or group of individuals on the basis of alleles, haplotypes, SNPs using high througput sequencing techniques.

label.value: epitope specific tolerance induction by T cells

definition.value: A process of tolerance induction by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: innate behavior design

definition.value: A study design in which the innate behavior of the organism is examined, e.g. path finding in bees.

label.value: detection of specific nucleic acids with complementary probes assay measuring epitope specific transforming growth factor-beta production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific transforming growth factor-beta production by T cells that uses a detection of specific nucleic acids with complementary probes assay.

label.value: SNP microarray

definition.value: A DNA microarray used to detect polymorphisms in DNA samples

label.value: cell component comparison design

definition.value: A study design that compares samples from different cell components.

label.value: ELISPOT assay measuring epitope specific granulocyte macrophage colony-stimulating factor production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific granulocyte macrophage colony stimulating factor production by T cells that uses an ELISPOT assay.

label.value: epitope specific macrophage inflammatory protein-1 alpha production by T cells

definition.value: A process of macrophage inflammatory protein-1 alpha production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: epitope specific T cell activation

definition.value: A process of T cell activation resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-10 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-10 production by T cells.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific transforming growth factor-beta production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific transforming growth factor-beta production by T cells that uses a cytometric bead array assay.

label.value: ex vivo design

definition.value: A study design where all or part of an organism is removed and studied in vitro, e.g. part of a mouse is removed and cultured in vitro. A cell culture with an established cell line is an in vitro experiment.

label.value: epitope specific type IV hypersensitivity by T cells

definition.value: A process of type IV hypersensitivity by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: normalization testing design

definition.value: A study design that tests different normalization procedures.

label.value: intracellular material detection assay measuring epitope specific perforin release

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific perforin release assay that uses an intracellular material detection by flow cytometry assay.

label.value: cell culture analyte detection bioassay measuring epitope specific interleukin-2 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific interleukin-2 production by T cells that uses a cell culture analyte detection bioassay.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-22 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-22 production by T cells.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-8 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-8 production by T cells.

label.value: epitope specific chemokine (C-C motif) ligand 1 production by T cells

definition.value: A process of chemokine (C-C motif) ligand 1 production by T cells resulting from the recognition of a T cell epitope.

label.value: cell culture analyte detection bioassay measuring epitope specific interleukin-10 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific interleukin-10 production by T cells that uses a cell culture analyte detection bioassay.

label.value: ChIP-chip by SNP array assay

definition.value: A ChIP-ChIP assay in which immunoprecipitated chromatin is run on a SNP array to detect polymorphism specific DNA elements in the isolated chromatin

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific RANTES production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific RANTES production by T cells that uses an ELISA.

label.value: cytometric bead array assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-1 beta production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific interleukin-1 beta production by T cells that uses a cytometric bead array assay.

label.value: genetic population background information

definition.value: a genetic characteristics information which is a part of genotype information that identifies the population of organisms

label.value: environmental history design

definition.value: A study design in which some aspect of the organism's environmental history is studied, such as exposure to teratogen, radiation, climate etc.

label.value: ELISPOT assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-6 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific interleukin-6 production by T cells that uses an ELISPOT assay.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific helper T cell enhancement of a B cell mediated immune response

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific helper activity assay that detects the ability of a T cell epitope to enhance an antibody response.

label.value: plasmon resonance assay measuring the dissociation constant [KD] of a T cell epitope:MHC:TCR complex

definition.value: A T cell epitope equilibrium dissociation constant (KD) determination assay that uses a surface plasmon resonance assay.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-5 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-5 production by T cells.

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific transforming growth factor-beta production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific transforming growth factor-beta production by T cells that uses an ELISA.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific RANTES production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects RANTES production by T cells.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific granulocyte macrophage colony stimulating factor production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects granulocyte macrophage colony stimulating factor production by T cells.

label.value: epigenetic modification identification objective

definition.value: A molecular feature identification objective that aims to detect epigenetic modifications, such as DNA methylation, histone modifications.

label.value: transcription profiling by tiling array assay

definition.value: A transcription profiling by array assay that uses a tiling path array.

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific interleukin-22 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific interleukin-22 production by T cells that uses an ELISA.

label.value: biological activity assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-21 production by T cells

definition.value: A T cell epitope specific cytokine production assay that detects interleukin-21 production by T cells.

label.value: ELISA measuring epitope specific interleukin-9 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific interleukin-9 production by T cells that uses an ELISA.

label.value: transcription profiling by high throughput sequencing design

definition.value: A study design in which sequencing technology (e.g. Solexa/454) is used to generate RNA sequence, analyse the transcibed regions of the genome, and/or to quantitate transcript abundance

label.value: intracellular cytokine staining assay measuring epitope specific interleukin-6 production by T cells

definition.value: An assay of epitope specific interleukin-6 production by T cells that uses an intracellular cytokine staining assay.
